title: Former GM VP Larry Burns, Domino's EVP Lynn Liddle Discuss Autonomous Transportation at National Press Club
text:
National Press Club
WASHINGTON , Oct. 5, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- Former GM Chief Technology Officer (CTO) Larry Burns and Domino's Pizza EVP Lynn Liddle will discuss the future of autonomous vehicles and their implications for businesses and America's economic security at a National Press Club Newsmakers news conference on Wednesday October 14 th , at 10:00 a.m. EDT . Energy Security expert Robby Diamond , CEO of Securing America's Future Energy (SAFE) will join Burns and Liddle.
This Newsmakers news conference will be held in the club's Bloomberg Room , on the 13 th floor of the National Press Building, 529 14 th St. NW, Washington , D.C.
Oil dependence is exacerbated by the myriad inefficiencies of the country's transportation system. Vehicle autonomy – and the new opportunities for improved efficiency and the sharing economy – will play a major role in determining the future of American mobility for both individuals and businesses.
Like all Newsmakers events, this news conference is open to credentialed media and NPC members, free of charge. No advance registration is required.
Contact: Frank Maisano , NPC Newsmakers Committee/host, 202 828-5864, frank.maisano@bgllp.com ; Herb Perone , NPC Newsmakers Chair, 301-512-7636, herb@peronecomm.com
